So you think people
are the problem?

22:16.718 --> 22:19.019
Yes, people are
absolutely the problem.

22:19.021 --> 22:21.757
Like, I wanna get away
from all the people.

22:24.260 --> 22:25.594
I could take a vacation.

22:26.728 --> 22:27.564
Go to the beach.

22:29.432 --> 22:30.766
Sand in the toes.

22:32.102 --> 22:33.869
Sun rising above the Gulf.

22:35.238 --> 22:37.671
Is there such a thing
as a vacation from people?

22:37.673 --> 22:40.408
Like, get me away
from all the people

22:40.410 --> 22:42.445
for a little bit, I'm good.

22:48.284 --> 22:49.783
Is that what you truly want?

22:49.785 --> 22:51.554
I truly want that, yes.

22:52.455 --> 22:53.256
Manifest it.

22:55.958 --> 22:57.458
Manifest it.

22:57.460 --> 23:00.230
You put it out in the universe,
and it becomes reality.

23:01.531 --> 23:03.397
- Yeah?
- Mmhmm.

23:03.399 --> 23:04.234
Okay.

23:08.804 --> 23:13.407
Oh, cosmic universe, unburden me

23:13.409 --> 23:18.078
from the plague of
societal obligation.

23:18.080 --> 23:20.716
Rid the planet of
all the people.

23:23.253 --> 23:26.054
I eschew the naysayers,
and the critics,

23:27.756 --> 23:31.561
and let me live out my
final days in solitude.

23:32.495 --> 23:33.329
With Barry.

23:36.798 --> 23:40.170
Did it work?

23:42.838 --> 23:44.338
I don't, I really don't know,

23:44.340 --> 23:46.174
cause I don't speak the
language of the universe.

23:46.176 --> 23:47.908
Oh my.

23:47.910 --> 23:49.912
Well, it's worth a shot.

23:55.117 --> 23:56.816
Did you have
any dreams last night?

23:56.818 --> 23:58.685
Yes, one.

23:58.687 --> 24:00.588
- You were a turtle.
- I've always wanted

24:00.590 --> 24:03.426
- to be a turtle.
- And I was a dove.

24:05.160 --> 24:08.296
But I was in a house, in a
cage, and you were outside,

24:08.298 --> 24:10.130
and you weren't in a cage.

24:10.132 --> 24:14.302
But you were walking by,
slowly, because you're a turtle.

24:14.304 --> 24:16.038
And I was singing like an angel.

24:17.340 --> 24:18.939
And you heard me
through an open window,

24:18.941 --> 24:20.106
and you fell in love with me,

24:20.108 --> 24:22.510
even though you couldn't see me.

24:22.512 --> 24:23.843
And you were outside and free,

24:23.845 --> 24:25.546
and could do
whatever you wanted.

24:25.548 --> 24:29.650
Go to Greece, or Antarctica.

24:29.652 --> 24:32.852
- Do turtles like the cold?
- Doesn't matter,

24:32.854 --> 24:34.988
cause you didn't go.

24:34.990 --> 24:36.823
You started climbing the
front stairs of the house,

24:36.825 --> 24:37.793
straight to me.

24:39.828 --> 24:41.362
But your little turtle
legs were too short

24:41.364 --> 24:43.364
to make it up the stairs.

24:43.366 --> 24:44.866
But you tried, anyway.

24:47.069 --> 24:47.903
Forever.

24:50.906 --> 24:52.140
Until you died.

24:54.410 --> 24:56.144
I don't think I
like your dream.

24:58.381 --> 25:01.049
Well it's my dream, not yours.

25:03.386 --> 25:04.219
True.

25:19.335 --> 25:21.269
Hey, babe, I think they forgot

25:21.271 --> 25:23.337
to deliver the
paper this morning.

25:23.339 --> 25:25.238
I'm gonna run to the store.

25:25.240 --> 25:26.074
Okay.

27:30.899 --> 27:32.535
- Hey babe?
- Mmhmm?

27:33.803 --> 27:35.036
Is it a holiday?

27:36.371 --> 27:37.473
Nope.

27:46.381 --> 27:48.582
Weird.

27:48.584 --> 27:49.419
Why?

27:50.853 --> 27:54.254
Well, the store was closed,
and there's nobody outside.

27:54.256 --> 27:55.591
What do you mean, nobody?

28:41.303 --> 28:42.137
Steve?

29:50.973 --> 29:53.541
Hi, this is Jamie,
with Artists' Space gallery.

29:53.543 --> 29:55.678
Leave me a message and
I'll call you back.

29:57.345 --> 29:58.548
Straight to voicemail.

30:35.651 --> 30:36.719
It's impossible.

30:37.987 --> 30:38.754
Apparently not.

30:42.157 --> 30:44.492
But, we were joking.

30:45.661 --> 30:47.029
It was a joke!

30:48.096 --> 30:48.898
Evidently not.

30:56.739 --> 30:59.107
Was, was there an evacuation?

31:02.243 --> 31:04.446
We would've heard
about it, wouldn't we?

31:17.927 --> 31:19.394
Maybe, we're hallucinating.

31:23.231 --> 31:25.300
We're both hallucinating
the same thing?

31:37.245 --> 31:38.413
Maybe it's a dream.

31:40.281 --> 31:45.286
And my mind is telling me
you're here, and I can feel you,

31:49.659 --> 31:51.994
but I can't actually feel you.

31:56.065 --> 31:56.832
Maybe?

32:00.502 --> 32:02.772
No, but when you
dream, you don't,

32:03.839 --> 32:05.139
you don't know
you're having a dream

32:05.141 --> 32:06.439
when you're in the dream.

32:06.441 --> 32:08.610
You don't know you had a
dream until you wake up.

32:11.279 --> 32:12.948
And you've already
had it, right?

32:14.950 --> 32:16.950
Then what the fuck is it?

33:57.887 --> 33:58.686
Fuck.

35:29.777 --> 35:30.612
Hey Bar?

35:31.813 --> 35:32.647
Barry.

35:34.884 --> 35:35.717
Bar.

35:54.535 --> 35:55.371
Barry?

36:36.678 --> 36:37.512
Phyl?

36:38.513 --> 36:39.348
Phyl?

36:40.581 --> 36:42.418
Oh my God!

36:45.720 --> 36:47.222
What's goin' on?

36:51.360 --> 36:53.726
Why is your hair wet?

36:53.728 --> 36:55.395
Did you know there's a
creek behind the house?

36:55.397 --> 36:57.366
- What?
- It's wild.

37:08.410 --> 37:10.578
If this is what
the world is like,

37:12.247 --> 37:14.083
then we're all that we have.

37:16.452 --> 37:18.553
I know, I know.

37:49.617 --> 37:50.850
Now what do we do?

37:57.625 --> 37:59.792
Whatever the fuck we want.

39:13.168 --> 39:14.733
Tell me a story.

39:14.735 --> 39:16.505
About what?

39:17.339 --> 39:19.738
Anything.

39:19.740 --> 39:20.576
Okay.

39:23.345 --> 39:25.247
Mm, got it.

39:26.881 --> 39:28.747
This is an old one, so
stop me if you've heard it.

39:28.749 --> 39:29.585
'Kay.

39:33.355 --> 39:35.455
It was a particularly
uneventful night,

39:35.457 --> 39:37.022
in the dead of winter.

39:37.024 --> 39:39.259
A man was traveling
along a mountain path,

39:39.261 --> 39:41.428
when the breeze
boasted to the hot sun,

39:41.430 --> 39:44.264
that it was truly the
stronger of the two.

39:44.266 --> 39:47.267
I can topple
trees, bury ships in the sea,

39:47.269 --> 39:50.403
and raise tidal waves larger
than the tallest mountains,

39:50.405 --> 39:54.039
that can devastate even
the mightiest of cities.

39:54.041 --> 39:55.875
The sun laughed.

39:55.877 --> 39:57.310
And of course, we
all know that the sun

39:57.312 --> 39:59.613
is the most powerful
thing in the solar system.

39:59.615 --> 40:00.449
Right.

40:01.416 --> 40:03.452
You dare tempt me, Wind?

40:04.386 --> 40:07.420
See that weary man, far below?

40:07.422 --> 40:10.923
Let us see who can take
the coat off that man.

40:10.925 --> 40:14.561
If you can, you are
truly the greatest.

40:14.563 --> 40:16.496
That is simple.

40:16.498 --> 40:19.166
The breeze
swelled, and blew hard.

40:19.168 --> 40:22.101
The man clung hard to his
coat, and no matter how strong

40:22.103 --> 40:24.304
the wind blew, he
never relented.

40:24.306 --> 40:26.972
He only shivered,
pulled his coat tighter.

40:26.974 --> 40:29.909
The sun stepped out from
behind a cloud, and grew.

40:29.911 --> 40:32.978
Its heat warmed the air,
and the frosty ground.

40:32.980 --> 40:34.447
The snow melted.

40:34.449 --> 40:37.584
The leaves of the trees
shriveled, and turned to dust.

40:37.586 --> 40:41.655
The man grew hot, and sought
refuge in the shade of a hill.

40:41.657 --> 40:44.624
He took off his
coat, and rested.

40:44.626 --> 40:46.528
The breeze was dumbfounded.

40:47.529 --> 40:50.630
How did you do that?

40:50.632 --> 40:53.935
Not with force,
but with gentleness.

40:58.973 --> 41:00.473
Then what?

41:00.475 --> 41:04.346
Well, that's kinda the
end of the story, I guess.

41:05.813 --> 41:07.048
But what about the man?

41:08.849 --> 41:10.718
He dies, eventually.

41:11.819 --> 41:12.820
Shit.

41:21.896 --> 41:23.463
I'd be doing a show,

41:23.465 --> 41:26.335
and I would remember everything
about the performance,

41:27.302 --> 41:29.001
leading up to it.

41:29.003 --> 41:30.970
And then I would
sort of, come to,

41:30.972 --> 41:33.072
as the audience was clapping.

41:33.074 --> 41:37.142
Like there was a void in my
memory of the entire show.

41:37.144 --> 41:38.744
Kinda like when
you're driving,

41:38.746 --> 41:40.313
and you get to your destination,

41:40.315 --> 41:41.681
but you don't
remember the drive?

41:41.683 --> 41:43.050
Yeah, like that.

41:44.686 --> 41:46.688
There's a sorta high, I guess.

41:49.890 --> 41:50.858
That's what I liked.

41:52.394 --> 41:54.361
You could perform for me.

41:54.363 --> 41:55.196
A private show?

41:56.665 --> 41:58.598
The whole
world's our private show.

41:58.600 --> 41:59.401
Huh.

42:03.372 --> 42:05.672
I should've picked a
more manly profession.

42:05.674 --> 42:07.840
Like a hunter.

42:07.842 --> 42:09.278
Or a lumberjack.

42:27.962 --> 42:31.130
Have you ever climbed a tree?

42:31.132 --> 42:33.098
You don't think I can?

42:33.100 --> 42:35.470
- Mm.
- Watch this.

42:38.105 --> 42:41.576
Yeah,
what's your first step?

42:46.213 --> 42:49.316
It's a gesture.

42:49.318 --> 42:52.987
You invite the viewer
to move about the piece.

42:55.657 --> 42:57.258
They become an explorer.

42:58.627 --> 43:01.728
Dipping in and out of
thought, through the nooks

43:01.730 --> 43:06.735
and the crannies, shifting in
and out of light, and color.

43:11.773 --> 43:13.906
It's not meant to be one thing,

43:13.908 --> 43:17.746
but a complex collection
of a variety of thoughts.

43:18.979 --> 43:23.452
Like a troubled, noisy
mind, frozen in a moment.

43:25.754 --> 43:28.357
The individual pieces
alone, are unique.

43:29.758 --> 43:34.128
And taken in as a whole can
seem messy, but take a step back

43:36.130 --> 43:38.600
and the whole of the thing
comes together as one.

43:51.513 --> 43:54.848
Wait, I think
I know where we are.

43:54.850 --> 43:56.483
Oh yeah?

43:56.485 --> 43:58.350
I know
this smell anywhere.

43:58.352 --> 44:00.522
Okay, open 'em.

44:02.356 --> 44:04.990
Oh yeah, it definitely
smells like mildew

44:04.992 --> 44:06.026
and urine in here.

44:06.994 --> 44:07.863
Wait for it.

44:14.001 --> 44:16.471
Your co-star.

44:17.873 --> 44:22.878
Okay, what
do you wanna see?

44:23.412 --> 44:24.677
Anything.

44:24.679 --> 44:27.014
Maybe something you
remember from before.

44:28.750 --> 44:32.987
All right, um, oh, I got it.

44:34.922 --> 44:36.924
The scene takes place
outside of a cafe.

44:37.859 --> 44:39.492
I was waiting.

44:39.494 --> 44:41.728
I was waiting on you, actually.

44:41.730 --> 44:44.163
And this stranger came up to me.

44:44.165 --> 44:48.002
She said, uh, well she said

44:49.538 --> 44:50.770
"Excuse me,

44:50.772 --> 44:53.338
"do you know what
time brunch ends?"

44:53.340 --> 44:56.375
And I was like, I don't know.

44:56.377 --> 44:59.046
And she said "You don't know?"

45:01.015 --> 45:02.114
No.

45:02.116 --> 45:03.750
"How can you work at a
place that serves brunch

45:03.752 --> 45:05.117
"and not even know
what time it ends?

45:05.119 --> 45:07.186
"Isn't that like your
one fucking job?"

45:07.188 --> 45:08.120
I don't work here.

45:08.122 --> 45:10.122
"You look like you work here."

45:10.124 --> 45:11.390
What?

45:11.392 --> 45:12.625
"You're wearing
that black shirt,

45:12.627 --> 45:14.261
"and you're standing
by the door, so..."

45:16.397 --> 45:19.634
If I worked here, wouldn't
I be inside, working?

45:20.869 --> 45:22.301
"Look man, I don't know you,

45:22.303 --> 45:24.369
"you could be on your
break or something."

45:24.371 --> 45:25.572
I'm just waiting for someone.

45:25.574 --> 45:28.475
"Oh my God, would you calm down?

45:28.477 --> 45:30.543
"It's just a simple
fucking question."

45:30.545 --> 45:32.110
To somebody that
doesn't know the answer.

45:32.112 --> 45:35.082
"Jesus, Yelp was right,
this place is horrible.

45:36.818 --> 45:38.317
"And you know what, just go back

45:38.319 --> 45:41.253
"to whatever shithole you came
from, you fuckin' tourist."

45:41.255 --> 45:42.589
But I was born here.

45:42.591 --> 45:44.624
I'm from here.

45:44.626 --> 45:46.759
Maybe the hipster
girl's right.

45:46.761 --> 45:50.095
Maybe we should
go somewhere else.

45:50.097 --> 45:50.932
Get away.

45:53.568 --> 45:54.401
Maybe.

46:25.499 --> 46:27.301
Hey, have you
seen my blue velvet?

46:28.637 --> 46:29.470
Bar?

46:30.605 --> 46:32.137
What?

46:32.139 --> 46:34.141
My blue
velvet, have you seen it?

46:35.175 --> 46:36.310
No, uh, I don't know.

47:01.570 --> 47:03.002
All right, let's
get out of here.

47:03.004 --> 47:04.003
You wanna take this?

47:04.005 --> 47:06.505
No, nah, go ahead and grab it.

47:06.507 --> 47:07.474
I'll paint over it.

47:24.960 --> 47:26.224
What if there's
somebody out there,

47:26.226 --> 47:28.395
and we don't even know it?

47:30.765 --> 47:32.199
Where would they be?

47:34.268 --> 47:35.336
I don't know.

47:36.403 --> 47:37.739
Where would
we even start looking?

47:41.375 --> 47:42.611
I don't know.

47:48.282 --> 47:49.216
Racist people.

47:52.020 --> 47:52.854
Children.

47:54.889 --> 47:55.890
Stockbrokers.

47:57.458 --> 47:59.391
Bill Gates.

47:59.393 --> 48:00.561
And Mel Gibson.

48:05.399 --> 48:07.201
All of North Korea.

48:11.238 --> 48:13.975
Every artist
you've ever known.

48:20.414 --> 48:24.986
And every actor,
and every director,

48:26.220 --> 48:27.419
and every scientist,

48:27.421 --> 48:29.758
and politician,
and schoolteacher.

48:35.229 --> 48:37.431
All the shitty ones,
and all the good ones.

50:06.720 --> 50:09.858
Man, being an astronomer's kind
of a bullshit job, isn't it?

50:12.693 --> 50:15.562
Like, all they do
is look at stuff,

50:17.031 --> 50:18.933
and then write
down what they saw.

50:20.835 --> 50:25.672
Like, oh look, that star
just exploded, write it down.

50:29.710 --> 50:33.547
I mean, sometimes,
that's all you have to do.

50:35.716 --> 50:39.788
You observe, and then interpret.

51:20.228 --> 51:22.263
Well, I guess that
was inevitable.

52:15.482 --> 52:16.317
Phyl?

52:18.052 --> 52:18.953
Come inside.

52:19.820 --> 52:24.825
Okay.

52:25.659 --> 52:26.858
What are we doin' in a tent?

52:26.860 --> 52:29.628
Actually, it's an
ancient Inuit structure,

52:29.630 --> 52:32.697
designed to keep us warm and
safe from the outside elements

52:32.699 --> 52:34.399
of the arctic tundra.

52:34.401 --> 52:38.137
I know, it's made of ice, so
you'd think it'd be freezing,

52:38.139 --> 52:40.174
but actually it
keeps the warmth in.

52:41.075 --> 52:42.174
I feel it.

52:42.176 --> 52:43.044
Oh, wait for it.

52:44.979 --> 52:46.747
I found this little guy outside.

52:48.882 --> 52:50.548
How d'you think he got here?

52:50.550 --> 52:54.853
Oh, probably just went
for a walk, got lost,

52:54.855 --> 52:57.089
wandered around for a bit,
and next thing he knew,

52:57.091 --> 52:58.026
he was in the cold.

52:59.027 --> 52:59.860
Poor little guy.

53:36.397 --> 53:37.562
What
are we doing here?

53:37.564 --> 53:39.798
Escaping
the elements.

53:39.800 --> 53:41.800
We can't
stay in here forever.

53:41.802 --> 53:43.102
Why not?

53:43.104 --> 53:43.937
We just can't.

53:45.906 --> 53:46.740
We'll die.

53:48.042 --> 53:49.210
I gotta get outta here.

54:02.756 --> 54:04.158
Please don't die before me.

54:06.094 --> 54:07.161
We could die together.

54:10.897 --> 54:12.300
Wanna make a suicide pact?

54:16.603 --> 54:20.441
If you died, I would
die of a broken heart.

54:22.143 --> 54:25.144
We'd be like, wrapped
in each others' arms,

54:25.146 --> 54:26.513
like the statues at Pompeii.

54:27.781 --> 54:29.148
I don't think there
were any like that.

54:29.150 --> 54:30.318
Of course there were.

54:32.953 --> 54:35.154
They did find a
guy masturbating.

54:37.958 --> 54:39.258
It happened.

54:39.260 --> 54:41.360
Okay, but you don't
have to talk about it

54:41.362 --> 54:42.763
when we're having a moment.

54:43.697 --> 54:46.499
Well what do you want from me?

54:46.501 --> 54:48.334
What's your problem?

54:48.336 --> 54:49.667
Nothing.

54:49.669 --> 54:50.835
I'm just not
excited about death.

54:50.837 --> 54:52.473
I didn't say that you were.

54:54.875 --> 54:56.044
Just fantasizing.

54:57.178 --> 54:59.111
Well death isn't
somethin' to joke about.

54:59.113 --> 55:00.114
I'm not joking.

55:01.215 --> 55:02.682
When did you get so morbid?

55:04.152 --> 55:05.552
I'm not morbid.

55:12.527 --> 55:15.229
It's like you don't even
wonder what this is all about.

55:16.563 --> 55:21.469
You sit around and turn
this over and over and over,

55:22.170 --> 55:25.337
trying to figure it out.

55:25.339 --> 55:29.874
But the truth is, that
we're never gonna know.

55:29.876 --> 55:33.747
So just snap out of it.

55:37.651 --> 55:39.120
I'm not like you, Phyl.

55:42.490 --> 55:43.857
I can't just turn on a dime.

55:47.528 --> 55:51.698
I can't help but feel the
burden that I was left behind.

55:55.735 --> 55:57.271
Those thoughts are insidious.

56:14.721 --> 56:16.957
I'm surrounded by so much stuff.

56:18.559 --> 56:20.792
But for some reason, it feels
like I'm standing in a room

56:20.794 --> 56:24.198
full of nothing, all the time.

56:28.101 --> 56:29.237
I'm there, too.

56:34.375 --> 56:38.246
Hey, hey!

56:40.481 --> 56:42.216
All I ever wanted
was to be happy.

56:44.651 --> 56:47.453
I thought that's
what you wanted, too.

56:47.455 --> 56:49.455
- I do, but...
- No buts.

56:49.457 --> 56:50.922
- Yeah, but...
- Barry!

56:50.924 --> 56:53.592
It's like you don't remember
what a shithole it was.

56:53.594 --> 56:54.493
I remember.

56:54.495 --> 56:56.127
Well, do you wanna go back

56:56.129 --> 56:57.797
to all that shit
that we endured?

56:58.965 --> 57:02.068
Back to that place
that didn't want us?

57:05.906 --> 57:07.439
Fuck it all.

57:07.441 --> 57:08.509
That's why we're here.

57:11.579 --> 57:16.584
Fuck the electricity, and
the cars, and buildings.

57:18.752 --> 57:19.953
We don't need any of it.

57:22.256 --> 57:23.422
We don't need the critics,

57:23.424 --> 57:25.293
and we don't need
the shitty directors.

57:27.794 --> 57:28.629
Fuck it all.

57:31.632 --> 57:32.799
Fuck it all.

57:34.602 --> 57:35.436
Come on.

57:57.625 --> 57:59.159
Did we go the wrong way?

58:02.862 --> 58:03.830
I don't think so.

58:06.701 --> 58:09.736
But, shouldn't we be
closer to the house by now?

58:20.847 --> 58:24.015
I guess, I guess
let's just keep goin'.

58:54.114 --> 58:56.016
Maybe we
took a wrong turn.

59:00.421 --> 59:01.422
Should we go back?

59:03.256 --> 59:05.359
I don't honestly
know which way is back.

59:10.964 --> 59:15.969
